# KOK Practice — Stack & Conventions

## Package manager
Always use **pnpm**. Never suggest npm or yarn commands.

## Formatting (Biome)
- Single quotes for strings
- 2-space indentation
- Semicolons always
- Trailing commas ES5
- Imports organised at top of file (no inline imports)

## Next.js App Router
- Server Components by default — add `'use client'` only when interactivity/hooks are needed
- Server Actions live in `actions/` with `'use server'` directive
- Use `lib/supabase/server.ts` in Server Components and Server Actions
- Use `lib/supabase/client.ts` in Client Components only

## TypeScript
- Strict mode — no implicit `any` in database code
- Use types from `types/database.ts` (Quest, Answer, Kateg, Numbs, QuestWithAnswers)
- Exhaustive switch: add `never` check in default case for union/enum switches

## Tailwind CSS 4
- Use CSS variables defined in `app/globals.css` via `var(--color-*)` tokens
- Merge classes with `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`
- No inline style attributes for theming — use Tailwind utilities

## Data fetching
- Server Components: fetch directly with Supabase server client
- Client Components: use TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`)
- Never fetch Supabase data directly in event handlers — use Server Actions or Query functions
